// Motor would go past the desired angle and recorrect itself. 
// Not ideal movement. 


/*


---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6th May 
Project succesful : 30 seconds to complete the job. 

Optimization occurs: 
    Lower delays between each instruction 
    Gaurdrails deploying at the same time. 
    Using a timer to have measure the duration of motors such that we have many motors running at once.
        Using a block wise sequence. 

    Potentiometer to optimise the shoulder angles. 


Outcomes: 
    - Achieved a time of 15s using lower time delays. However body requires weight to prevent it from mis aligning. 
    - servos deploy at the same time even though they are powered by 2 different pins.



-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7th May 
Project Status : ~15 seconds 

Notes on Code with the timer: 
    - Structered into 3 main block for testing and debugging the process. 
    - Coded with optimisation/speed in mind. Lower number of instructions performed. (Comparions take lower time than digital writes)
    - considered Memory capacity too. Used 'byte' where applicable as it requires lower memory than 'int'. 
    - Max two motors/servos run at a time to prevent excessive current usage. 


Test Results: 
    - Sequence works. 
    - Short Arm requires vlong delays : Probably due to faulty Short arms. As it heated up and the motors run rough. 


Optimization/For next testing: 
    - 1 Motor driver runs Elbows. Other driver runs shoulders. 
            This prevents the motor drive from drawing too much current as one elbow + one shoulder runs at a single time. 

